cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use PyPyrus Map in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "PyPyrus Map"
abstract: "A Python tool for visualizing metabolic reaction neighborhoods in COBRApy-compatible genome-scale models. Generates publication-quality figures of metabolite neighborhoods including heterologous and non-native pathways, with optional flux overlay from FBA solutions."
authors:
  - family-names: Rihan
    given-names: Nourelden
    orcid: https://orcid.org/0009-0005-0466-8029
version: 0.1.1
date-released: "2026-03-05"
license: MIT
repository-code: https://github.com/NoureldenRihan/PyPyrus-Map
url: https://github.com/NoureldenRihan/PyPyrus-Map
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.18870982
keywords:
  - metabolic engineering
  - genome-scale model
  - COBRApy
  - flux balance analysis
  - metabolic visualization
  - synthetic biology
  - bioinformatics
acknowledgements: >
  PyPyrus Map was developed with the assistance of Claude (Anthropic),
  a large language model used for code generation and implementation.
  All research direction, architectural decisions, and feature design
  were conceived and directed by the author. Developed as part of
  Project Menhed, an in silico metabolic engineering initiative
  targeting lycopene biosynthesis optimization.
